Create a Waterfall Segment

If you’re running a campaign with multiple offers, use a waterfall segment to create a hierarchical structure consisting of subsegments. Each subsegment is a refinement of the previous one. You can reorder the subsegments to reflect the priority relative to each other and to prioritize subsegments when a customer exists in more than one segment.

Available with add-on license: Segmentation and Activation
In Data Cloud, click Segments.
Click New.
Select Use a Visual Builder.
Select Waterfall Segment, and click Next.
Enter the segment details.
Select a data space.
For Segment On, select the data model object (DMO) that your segment is built on.
Give your waterfall segment a unique name that’s easily identifiable.
Click Next.
Define when and how often your waterfall segment publishes to activation targets.
If you plan to add segment filters, you can also select Don’t Refresh and add the schedule later. Subsegments follow the waterfall segment schedule. Rapid segment publish isn’t available for waterfall segments.
Click Save.
Create the waterfall by dragging segments onto the canvas and ordering them according to priority.
You can add up to 20 segments. Only active segments that are based on the selected DMO and that aren’t already in a waterfall are listed. A segment can exist in only one waterfall. You can't include nested segments in a waterfall segment. Subsegment counts are available after you save and publish the waterfall segment.
Click Save.
Saving your waterfall segment takes time. Leaving the waterfall page doesn’t affect processing.
EXAMPLE

You have four discounted offers, but you don’t want a customer to receive more than one offer. To target your campaign, create a prioritized list of mutually exclusive subsegments so that an audience member exists in only one subsegment and receives only one promotional offer.
